!! ### Morphophonology
!  ---------------

!! To represent phonologic variations in word forms we use the following
!! symbols in the lexicon files:

!! #### Archiphonemes

{aГӨ}  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**:  Vowel alternating symbol
{oГ¶}  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**:  Vowel alternating symbol 
{uГј}  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**:  Vowel alternating symbol
%^Рә2 %^Р»2 %^Рј2 %^СӮ2 %^СҢ2 %^Рҡ2 %^Рӣ2 %^Рң2 %^Рў2 %^Р¬2 %^Рҳ2  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**
%^V1       !!= * **@CODE@** for reduplicated vowel СғРҪР°У§РҪ > СғРҪР°Р°РҪ
%>   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**  suffix border
%{РёС–%}   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**:  for soft and hard
%{Р°СҸ%}   !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**:  for soft and hard

!! #### Triggers to control variation
{front} !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**:  Vowel change triggers
{back}  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**:  Vowel change triggers
%^Close !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** Close syllable, this triggers final consonant drop, seen in word-final position and before consonant
%^C2V   !!= * **@CODE@** Consonant v to vowel, Izhva РҪСӢСӢ, РҫРҫРҪСӢ

!! #### Valency tags, i.e. tags assigned to verbs for denoting their arbuments

+%<acc%>                  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** accusative
+%<ela%>                  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** elative -СӢСҒСҢ
+%<ins%>                  !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** instrumental -У§РҪ
+%<inf_РҪСӢ%>               !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** infinitive in -РҪСӢ
+%<po_РІСӢР»У§%>              !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** postposition РІСӢР»У§
+%<sub_РјСӢР№%>              !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** subordinate clause in РјСӢР№/that


!! ### Symbols that need to be escaped on the lower side (towards twolc):

 В»7     !! * В»
 В«7     !! * В«
 %[%>%] !! * \> (written with square brackets, see the root.lexc file)
 %[%<%] !! * < (written with square brackets, see the root.lexc file)


!! ## Flag diacritics

!! We have manually optimised the structure of our lexicon using following
!! flag diacritics to restrict morhpological combinatorics - only allow compounds
!! with verbs if the verb is further derived into a noun again:

!! | Flags | Explanation 
!! | ----- | ----------- 
 @P.NeedNoun.ON@    !!вүҲ |  **@CODE@** | (Dis)allow compounds with verbs unless nominalised
 @D.NeedNoun.ON@    !!вүҲ |  **@CODE@** | (Dis)allow compounds with verbs unless nominalised
 @C.NeedNoun@       !!вүҲ |  **@CODE@** | (Dis)allow compounds with verbs unless nominalised



!! Two flags copied from sme

!! | Flags | Explanation 
!! | ----- | ----------- 
 @P.Pmatch.Loc@       !!вүҲ |  **@CODE@** | Used on multi-token analyses; tell hfst-tokenise/pmatch where in the form/analysis the token should be split.
 @P.Pmatch.Backtrack@ !!вүҲ |  **@CODE@** | Used on single-token analyses; tell hfst-tokenise/pmatch to backtrack by reanalysing the substrings before and after this point in the form (to find combinations of shorter analyses that would otherwise be missed)


!! ### Compunding

!! #### Tags
+Cmp         !!вүҲ * **@CODE@**
+Cmp/Serial  !!вүҲ *  @CODE@ used with serial verbs
+Cmp/SplitR     !!вүҲ * **@CODE@** 


!! #### Flags 

!! For languages that allow compounding, the following flag diacritics are needed
!! to control position-based compounding restrictions for nominals. Their use is

!! handled automatically if combined with +CmpN/xxx tags. If not used, they will
!! do no harm.

!! | Flags | Explanation 
!! | ----- | ----------- 
 @P.CmpFrst.FALSE@ !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Require that words tagged as such only appear first
 @D.CmpPref.TRUE@  !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Block such words from entering ENDLEX
 @P.CmpPref.FALSE@ !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Block these words from making further compounds
 @D.CmpLast.TRUE@  !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Block such words from entering R
 @D.CmpNone.TRUE@  !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Combines with the next tag to prohibit compounding
 @U.CmpNone.FALSE@ !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Combines with the prev tag to prohibit compounding
 @P.CmpOnly.TRUE@  !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Sets a flag to indicate that the word has passed R
 @D.CmpOnly.FALSE@ !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Disallow words coming directly from root.

!! Use the following flag diacritics to control downcasing of derived proper
!! nouns (e.g. Finnish Pariisi -> pariisilainen). See e.g. North SГЎmi for how to use
!! these flags. There exists a ready-made regex that will do the actual down-casing
!! given the proper use of these flags.

!! | Flags | Explanation 
!! | ----- | ----------- 
 @U.Cap.Obl@        !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Always capital letter for names: Deatnu.
 @U.Cap.Opt@        !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Allowing downcasing of derived names: deatnulasj.


!! | Flags | Explanation 
!! | ----- | ----------- 
@U.CONJ-VAL.TV@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Flags used with serial verbs: VAL = Valence
@U.CONJ-VAL.IV@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | Flags used with serial verbs: VAL = Valence
@U.CONJ-INF.YES@         !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  INF = Infinitive
@U.CONJ-INF.NO@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  INF = Infinitive
@U.CONJ-TX.FUT@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  TX = tense
@U.CONJ-TX.PRES@         !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  TX = tense
@U.CONJ-TX.PRET1@        !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  TX = tense
@U.CONJ-TX.PRET2@        !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  TX = tense
@U.CONJ-GER.IG@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  GER = gerund
@U.CONJ-GER.VCAR@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  GER = VCar СӮУ§Рі
@U.CONJ-GER.VCARMoz@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  GER = VCar СӮУ§РіРјРҫР·
@U.CONJ-GER.VMON@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  GER = VMon РјУ§РҪ
@U.CONJ-GER.VTER@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** |  GER = VTer СӮУ§РҙР·
@U.CONJ-MX.IND@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | MX = mood
@U.CONJ-MX.IMP@          !!вүҲ | **@CODE@** | MX = mood
